-- 
Russian Stocks Advance as Oil Tops $111, Gold Reaches Record

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-04-08T07:54:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/russian-stocks-advance-as-oil-tops-111-gold-reaches-record.html
Russian stocks rose for the third
day this week as oil, the country’s main export earner, climbed
above $111 a barrel and gold advanced to an all-time high.  The  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  increased 0.3 percent to 1,849.62 as of
11:36 a.m. in Moscow, extending this week’s advance to 0.4
percent. OAO Polymetal, a Russian gold and silver producer, rose
1 percent, and OAO Gazprom, the country’s gas exporter,
increased 0.9 percent.  Crude for May delivery gained as much as $1.18 to $111.48
in New York, climbing for a third consecutive week. Futures
extended a rally to a 30-month high as the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization said forces loyal to  Muammar Qaddafi  caused a fire
at the Sarir oil field, Al Arabiya television reported
yesterday. The Libyan conflict is in a stalemate, according to
Army General Carter Ham, the U.S. commander for Africa,
threatening supplies from  Africa ’s third-largest oil producer.  Gold climbed as much as 0.6 percent to a record to
$1,467.07 an ounce. Copper, lead and nickel gained in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in London at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
